What about changing it to the following snippet to keep the logic in one place:

    file_paths = [os.path.join(path, file_name)]
    if check_for_exe:
        file_paths.append(file_paths[0] + '.exe')
    for file_path in file_paths:
        if os.path.isfile(file_path) and os.access(file_path, os.X_OK):
            return file_path

Added the following comment (and assert) to SBInterpolatedKImageImpl constructor:
```
        // Note that _dk is the pitch of realKImage and imagKImage.  In contrast, _stepk indicates
        // the maximum pitch for drawImage() to use when rendering an image, which may be set
        // larger than _dk for efficiency.
        assert(_stepk >= _dk);
```

I think this would probably be clearer by splitting into two nested matches, rather than having everything be one top-level match
```rust
match ... {
  Some(mock_operation) {
    let MockOperation { op: maybe_op, duration: maybe_duration } = mock_operation;
    if let Some(duration) = maybe_duration {
      sleep(d);
    }
    if let Some(op) = maybe_op {
      // send
    } else {
      drop(sink);
    }
  },
  None => // fail
}
```

